comment:
* Interface that defines a dialog-type class that can be shown, dismissed, or
 * canceled, and may have buttons that can be clicked.

variables.name: BUTTON_POSITIVE
variables.comment: The identifier for the positive button.

variables.name: BUTTON_NEGATIVE
variables.comment: The identifier for the negative button.

variables.name: BUTTON_NEUTRAL
variables.comment: The identifier for the neutral button.

methods.name: void cancel()
methods.comment:
* Cancels the dialog, invoking the {@link OnCancelListener}. *

* The {@link OnDismissListener} may also be called if cancellation * dismisses the dialog.

methods.name: void dismiss()
methods.comment: * Dismisses the dialog, invoking the {@link OnDismissListener}.
